Navid Saremi

Utrecht University 2018

Low Level GPU Characteristics.

In order to compile you need the HIP compiler and based on your device CUDA or HCC.

Please refer to https://github.com/ROCm-Developer-Tools/HIP/blob/master/INSTALL.md for installing the required tools for your system.

After installing the tools go to DeviceMicroBenchmarks directory and run make.

You can edit the main function in device_micro_benchmarks.cpp in order to select which benchmarks you desire. 
